reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars PNY SSD7CS900-240-RB: Turbocharged Performance for Your System!
reviews.reviewText: The PNY SSD7CS900-240-RB has taken my computing experience to a whole new level of speed and efficiency. This 2.5" SATA III Internal Solid State Drive (SSD) is a true game-changer, and here's why.First and foremost, the speed boost is nothing short of phenomenal. The 3D NAND technology delivers lightning-fast read and write speeds, significantly reducing boot times and application load times. It's like giving my system a turbocharged engine!The installation process was a breeze. The drive slotted in seamlessly, and the included migration software made transferring my data from my old drive a quick and hassle-free experience. Within minutes, I was up and running with the SSD.The improvement in system responsiveness is immediately noticeable. Tasks that used to take minutes are now completed in mere seconds. From opening applications to launching games, everything feels snappier and more fluid.The reliability of this SSD is commendable. It's clear that PNY has prioritized durability and longevity in the design. It's a reassuring feeling to know that my data is in safe hands with this reliable drive.Additionally, the drive's energy efficiency is a welcome bonus. It operates with lower power consumption compared to traditional HDDs, which not only extends battery life for laptops but also reduces overall energy costs for desktop systems.The drive's 240GB capacity is ample for my OS and essential applications, allowing me to maintain peak performance without sacrificing storage space.In terms of value, the PNY SSD7CS900-240-RB offers an excellent price-to-performance ratio. It's an investment that provides immediate and long-term benefits in terms of system speed and reliability.In summary, the PNY SSD7CS900-240-RB is a standout performer in the world of SSDs. Its blazing speed, ease of installation, and rock-solid reliability make it a top choice for anyone looking to supercharge their system's performance. If you're seeking a transformative upgrade for your computer, look no further than this exceptional SSD from PNY. It's a five-star investment that I wholeheartedly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works pretty well, was a good replacement for my PS5 hard drive
reviews.reviewText: This works great for replacing the hard drive on my PS4. It is pretty fast for a budgeted PS4 drive. It is thinner in height compared to most 2.5 disk drives but it will fit in your ps4 without much issues. I has a standard aluminum case and I had no trouble installing it. I did want to see how this would perform on on both Mac and PC so I tried it with that first also was my way to test the speed. The drive was able to work without any issues. It did not require any additional software and it was just a plug in play (minus the initialization. It also fit the sata port pretty well. The only thing I would say if you are installing this in laptops with a holder is that you may need to hold it up slightly as it is thinner than your normal 2.5 disk drive but honestly it would not be too much of a difference in installation. You always need to initalize it even with external. I did want to test the transfer speed using a 3.0 enclosure and the transfer speed is not too bad which is good. There was no extreme heat up to an alarming. I did a memory verification just to be safe and the storage memory is correct so you can be sure your data is safe. The speed works pretty well for my ps4. The games load faster and the PS4 does not lag during intense cut scenes which is what I wanted. I test it against some other 2.5 solid state drives (Samsung and WD) as well as the Seagate Hybrid drive and it was not bad. It is pretty on par with the most brand solid state drives. It is definitely a good drive to use for an upgrade from a disk drive to a higher capacity and faster storage. Unfortunately with so many games being big files 1 TB does fill up pretty quick. I was able to transfer all the data from my old PS4 drive to my new one but it did take time to back up and restore everything. Overall I like this drive. It has been reliable and fast. I have not had any issues with it slowing down or failing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cheap and good quality
reviews.reviewText: I've used these for a few years now, I've bought numerous ones in different sizes. They are fast (maybe not the fastest these days, but a definite upgrade over platter) and cheap. There's not much more to be said, if you want to cheaply upgrade a computer still running on platter drives, this is a great option for the storage portion of the upgrade. RAM would likely be the other thing if it's still running with 4gb of RAM. We use these at work as well for the same purpose and they buy us a lot of performance for little cost and reduce our need to fully replace older PCs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install, easy to setup, fast data transfer
reviews.reviewText: PNY CS900 2TB 3D NAND 2.5" SATA III Internal Solid State Drive (SSD) - (SSD7CS900-2TB-RB)The hard drive comes packaged in a retail hanging cardboard box. There are photos of the product and a lot of manufacturers' specs and info printed on the outside. Inside the box, the drive itself is cushioned in a molded plastic tray. There is no information or instruction sheet on the inside. The back of the box does note that it has a 3-year limited warranty, and if you wish details to go to the manufacturer's website.In my case, I'm not physically stalling this drive into a computer, I'm using it as an external storage device. Windows, of course did not recognize the hard drive immediately, since it is new and non-formatted. I barely had to initialize the drive and format the drive to NTFS so that it was usable for my storage.After setting up the drive, it worked normally for my storage needs.
